Calling `extension.to_string()` multiple times is inefficient. Consider storing it in a variable to avoid repeated allocations.

The code calls `extension.to_string()` twice on lines 40 and 47. Since `to_string()` allocates a new String each time, this is wasteful. A simple optimization would be:
```rust
let ext_str = extension.to_string();
if filename.len() <= ext_str.len() + 1 {
    // ...
}
let stem = &filename[..(filename.len() - (ext_str.len() + 1))];
```
This same pattern appears in `parsed_normalized_filename` as well (lines 95-103).
